  "title": "Staff Nurse (East / Kidney Dialysis / 5 days)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Profile</strong></p>\n<p>We are a well-established <strong>kidney care provider in Singapore</strong>, operating multiple community-based dialysis centres for over <strong>20 years</strong>. Our focus is on delivering <strong>safe, reliable, and compassionate renal care</strong>, supported by a team of dedicated nurses and healthcare professionals. As we continue to expand, we are looking for committed individuals who want to grow with us and make a meaningful impact in the community.</p>\n<p><strong>Work location: Bedok</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Working schedule: 5 days work week</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Rotating morning/afternoon shifts</li>\n  <li>Sunday permanently off</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Clinical Care &amp; Dialysis Procedures</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform      nursing assessments and ongoing evaluation of patients’ clinical      conditions.</li>\n  <li>Carry      out the full dialysis process: initiation, monitoring, troubleshooting,      and termination of treatment.</li>\n  <li>Ensure      proper setup, operation, and infection-control compliance for dialysis      machines and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Respond      appropriately to patient complications and provide necessary      interventions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Patient Education &amp; Support</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide      patient and caregiver education (e.g., diet, access care,      self-management).</li>\n  <li>Offer      emotional support and encourage rehabilitative progress.</li>\n  <li>Work      with multidisciplinary teams to ensure holistic care.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Documentation &amp; Centre Operations</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain      accurate nursing records, treatment charts, and incident documentation.</li>\n  <li>Uphold      safety, infection-control, and quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Contribute      to smooth centre operations, stock management, and workflow efficiency.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Key Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min.      NITEC/Diploma/Degree in Nursing and must be a <strong>Registered Nurse with      Singapore Nursing Board (SNB)</strong></li>\n  <li>Relevant      renal or dialysis experience preferred</li>\n  <li>Training      provided for candidates without prior dialysis experience</li>\n</ul>\n<p>📩 Your recruiter: <strong>WhatsApp your CV/resume to Celine</strong> at <strong>8977 7051 </strong>for a quicker response.</p>\n<p>You may also drop your resume via email to celinechan@envirodynamics.com.sg – only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Celine Chan I Reg. No: R21103433</p>\n<p>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte Ltd I EA License No.: 12C6285</p>",
